default estimated by 
defaultCharney
default in 1979 at 3.0
default ±1.5°C and that range remained more-or-less constant through all four previous IPCC reports.  
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHowever, during 2011-13, at least 16 peer-reviewed journal papers have used recent data and modern diagnostics to show that this historical ‘best estimate’ had been grossly over-stated. All find that the ‘most likely’ ECS figure is around 1.5-2°C – and lik
defaultely to be within a range of 1-3.5°C (not 1.5-4.5°C as applied in AR5). 
